snippet: For the second straight week, the Jets’ impotent offense was overshadowed by a critical player going down, this time Santonio Holmes, whose left foot buckled after he made a catch in the fourth quarter.
abstract: San Francisco 49ers defeat New York Jets, 34-0, exposing the lack of depth along the Jets' offensive live.
lead_paragraph: For the second straight week, the Jets’ impotent offense was overshadowed by a critical player going down, this time Santonio Holmes, whose left foot buckled after he made a catch in the fourth quarter.

headline.seo: Jets, Routed by 49ers, Lose Holmes to Injury
headline.main: A Rout Leaves the Jets Hurting and Cursing
